text: Le Malesherbois is a French commune. It is in the Loiret department. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Malesherbes (the seat), Coudray, Labrosse, Mainvilliers, Manchecourt, Nangeville and Orveau-Bellesauve.Arrêté préfectoral 30 November 2015 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Loiret
title: Le Malesherbois
